Necrotizing enterocolitis (NEC) treatment market can be segmented based on treatment type, end user, and region. In terms of treatment type, the market is divided into surgical treatment and pharmacological treatment. Surgical treatment involves procedures such as bowel resection or ostomy creation, while pharmacological treatment may include the use of antibiotics, probiotics, and vitamins to manage the condition. Regarding end users, the market caters to hospitals, surgical centers, and ambulatory surgical centers where NEC patients receive care. Geographically, key regions in the market include North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, Latin America, and the Middle East & Africa.

